evidence: The tensile stress-strain curve of BCC Nb10 after RHT at 900 °C for 1 min is depicted in Fig.  2 (a) , and the material properties are listed in Table . 1 . As-solution-treated Nb10 exhibited high strain hardening and ductility. Its hardness was 252 HV5, and its tensile properties were as follows: E = 70.5 GPa, yield strength (YS) = 524 MPa, ultimate tensile strength (UTS) = 704 MPa, and elongation (EL) = 17.5%.
The specimen aged at 450 °C for 36 had a hardness of 346 HV5 and the following tensile properties: E = 104.6 GPa, YS = 1031 MPa, UTS = 1085 MPa, and EL = 3%.
The specimen treatment at 500 °C for 36 h had the following properties: hardness = 274 HV5, E = 88.6 GPa, YS = 855 MPa, UTS = 892 MPa, and EL = 6%.
